text: Patissa ochreipalpalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by George Hampson in 1919. It is found on Mayotte off the coast of Southeast Africa. The wingspan is about . The forewings and hindwings are uniform silvery white.Annals and Magazine of Natural History (9) 4 (23): 318 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1919 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Patissa ochreipalpalis
